  {
    "Id": "188109",
    "ThreadId": "55497",
    "Html": "<p>I think your problem might be in how you're loading the skin, Im using the following in the App.xaml.cs:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;// Load application skin</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;var resources = (ResourceDictionary) Application.LoadComponent(new Uri(&quot;../Skins/default.xaml&quot;, UriKind.RelativeOrAbsolute));</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Current.Resources = resources;</p>\r\n<p>This loads the skin globally for the application, all other controls then inherit the styles using based on.</p>\r\n<p>I've also tested this injecting views using prism and it works like a charm. Let me know.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
    "PostedDate": "2009-05-08T06:32:41.407-07:00",
    "UserRole": null,
    "MarkedAsAnswerDate": null
